@Jane Wheelaghan
ENOLA Holmes was a character in a series of young adult mystery novels. The conceit was that she was the 20 years younger sister of Sherlock.  The books make a point of that ENOLA is ALONE spelled backwards. At least part of the time she is searching for her mother 
A couple of the books have been adapted into movies that were shown on Netflix a while back, which is also where the series Stranger Things (a big hit here in the US) was shown.  It centered on a group of kids in the 1980s, and Millie Bobbie Brown played one of the main characters.

